 at is there may be bad folks out there, but not all are that way.<br><br>Take Care all, and may the Christmas season bring you as much joy as you can handle<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47203">Treage Shadowbane</a></center> <br><center><b><u>~High Priest~</u></b></center> <br><center><a target="new" href="http://www.unitedindependent.com">United Independent</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uquistabris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quis Tabris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#E9D756>(12/23/01 10:47:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2822.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My Christmas Experiment</span><hr size=1> i had an experiance like that a few months ago...<br>i was running through Gfay and i saw this wood elf ranger and i saw this guy running around killing bats and stuff and i saw him chase this mob but it got away so i snared it and tossed him a SoW and he kept calling me sir and stuff...anyways i tossed him a few buffs and he asked me if my weapons where better then fine steel...i instantly had the &quot;i feel bad for this guy cause hes a newbie&quot; kinda feeling, i think i made his day by giving him my old ivy etched set i had rotting away.<br><br>there are good people who play this game, some have some real bad luck trying to get started, and if someone ever helped you as a newbie id say the best thing to do is atleast return that to someone else atleast once.<br><br> last i checked this ranger was well in his 20's...forgot his name tho. Kluryen 